The paper proposes a multi-objective genetic algorithm for the allocation of students to supervisors, which involves optimizing preferences on research/project topics, supervision quotas, and workload balance. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the optimization aspect, machine learning (cs.LG) for the use of genetic algorithms, robotics (cs.RO) for the potential application in robot learning, computer engineering (cs.CE) for the design of mutation and crossover operators, and software engineering (cs.SE) for the practical implementation of the allocation system.
